## When wiring SAML auth into an app

### Step 1 — Add module packs

**Backend:**

```typescript
import {ModulePackBE_SAML} from '@nu-art/saml-backend';
import {ApiDef_SAML} from '@nu-art/saml-shared';

// In Storm builder chain:
.addModulePack(ModulePackBE_SAML)

// In openApis array:
openApis: [ApiDef_SAML.loginSaml, ApiDef_SAML.assertSAML]
```

**Frontend:**

```typescript
import {ModulePackFE_SAML} from '@nu-art/saml-frontend';

// In Thunder builder chain:
.addModules(...ModulePackFE_SAML)
```

### Step 2 — Configure the SP

```typescript
ModuleBE_SAML: {
  spConfig: {
    entity_id: 'https://my-app.example.com/saml/metadata',
    assert_endpoint: 'https://my-app.example.com/v1/saml/assert',
    // Optional:
    certificate: '...SP certificate PEM...',
    private_key: '...SP private key PEM...',
  }
}
```

- `entity_id` — your SP's unique identifier (typically a URL).
- `assert_endpoint` — the full URL the IdP posts the SAML assertion to. Must match `ApiDef_SAML.assertSAML` path.

### Step 3 — Register SAML providers

Create `DB_SamlProvider` records in the database (via the admin UI `Page_SamlProviders` or programmatically):

```typescript
{
  domain: 'company.com',
  label: 'Company SSO',
  enabled: true,
  metadataUrl: 'https://idp.company.com/saml/metadata',
  idpEntityId: '...',       // auto-populated from metadata
  ssoLoginUrl: '...',       // auto-populated from metadata
  certificates: ['...'],    // auto-populated from metadata
}
```

Use `previewMetadata` to test a metadata URL before saving. Use `refreshMetadata` to re-fetch certificates when an IdP rotates them.

### Step 4 — Add SAML login UI

```typescript
import {Component_SamlLogin} from '@nu-art/saml-frontend';

// Email-based SAML login — user enters email, domain resolves the IdP:
<Component_SamlLogin />
```

For Google Workspace specifically:

```typescript
import {Component_GoogleSAMLLogin} from '@nu-art/saml-frontend';

<Component_GoogleSAMLLogin />
```

### Step 5 — Admin provider management

```typescript
import {Page_SamlProviders} from '@nu-art/saml-frontend';

// Add to your admin routes:
// Route: route_SamlProviders (exported from '@nu-art/saml-frontend')
```

This page provides CRUD for SAML providers with metadata preview and refresh.

